                    <p>The manual therapy (body work) used by Dr. Tanya Rampersad, ND uses osteopathic techniques (Visceral Manipulation, Neuromeningeal Manipulation) to assess and correct physical issues. The work is gentle and subtle, but often patients will feel releases,movement or gurgling. Virtually any tissue in the body can be addressed using these methods including the matrix of the bones, nerves, tendons, organs, ribs and supporting ligaments. The treatments should never be uncomfortable or painful but should put the client in a relaxed state.</p>
                    <p>The initial consultation (45 minutes) will include a thorough and detailed examination of the organs and glands using gentle palpation and subtle movement to assess positioning and function. The structures, glands and organs that are often assessed include:</p>
