                        <li style="list-style: square">Pancreas</li>
                        <li style="list-style: square">The cranium</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>At each visit (first visit and subsequent visits) the primary lesion is identified, released and balanced. The primary lesion is the site that is causing the most imbalance in the person at the moment. Lesions are often adhesions, scar tissue and ligament contractions, sometimes the lesion is an emotional disturbance. Usually second and third lesions can be addressed within the visit. Because the connective tissue is continuous throughout the entire body, small modifications at the most important site can affect comfort, mobility and flexibility in seemingly unconnected locations, for example, releasing the gallbladder may improve vertigo or shoulder pain or both.</p>
                    <p>Often a notable difference is evident immediately after treatment, but if there are multiple or more complex lesions, several visits may be required to achieve the desired results.</p>

